# Disowning a child process in POSIX shell

+Shell +POSIXShell +Snippet

How to create a child process which will not die when the parent process
terminates.

## Summary:

Double-fork the process (background a process already in a subshell):

```shell
( <cmd> & )
```

Or alternatively:

```shell
# On Linux
setsid <cmd>

# On OS X
nohup script -q -c '<cmd>' /dev/null &

```

[Source](https://stackoverflow.com/a/20338327)
